Forward target_compatible_with / tags through the mix_library macro.

The macro filters **kwargs to fixed allowlists and silently drops everything else, so a
`target_compatible_with` set on a mix_library reaches neither the `_mix_compile` target (which
resolves the Elixir toolchain) nor the `_mix_library_info` target (which carries the auto-added
`@hex_pm//:lib` dep). Without it on BOTH, a wildcard `bazel build //...` under the default
(non-Elixir) platform fails toolchain resolution — first on `<name>_compile`, then on
`@hex_pm//:lib_compile` reached via the info target's deps — instead of SKIPPING the package as
incompatible. Forwarding it to both targets makes the info target *directly* incompatible, which
prunes its (hex) deps before they are configured. B3 patch-in-place; lets the Elixir lane live
in-graph yet stay scoped to `--config=elixir`.

--- a/private/mix_library.bzl
+++ b/private/mix_library.bzl
@@ -387,4 +387,6 @@
         "deps",
         "include",
         "ez_deps",
+        "target_compatible_with",
+        "tags",
     )}
@@ -398,4 +400,6 @@
         "deps",
         "srcs",
         "include",
+        "target_compatible_with",
+        "tags",
     )}
